-- 
Peru Party Ends Talks Over Humala Government Role, Peru.21 Says

-- B y   B i l l   F a r i e s
-- 
2011-07-16T17:34:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-16/peru-party-ends-talks-over-humala-government-role-peru-21-says.html
The Peru Posible political party,
led by former President  Alejandro Toledo , has quit talks with
President-elect Ollanta Humala over a role in his future
government,  Peru.21  said, without identifying where it obtained
the information.  Toledo’s party won’t accept ministerial posts in Humala’s
government, which takes office July 28, the Lima-based newspaper
said on its website. Peru Posible will back Humala on some
issues in Congress, the newspaper said.  Luis Miguel Castilla, Peru’s departing deputy finance
minister, may be named economy minister under Humala, Peru.21
also said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bill Faries in  Buenos Aires  at 
